    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-23T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-23T21:00:00-05:00" n="55"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d55">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/3855: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-24T09:00:00+07:00"
                            >April 24, 1944—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 24—1:47 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>714. Drumright reports in telegram April 20 that total of 17 American evacuees
                    from Honan had arrived Sian (Embassy’s 626, April 8, 6 [<hi rend="italic"
                    >1</hi>] p.m.). By despatch April 16<note n="34" xml:id="d55fn34">Not
                        printed.</note> he reports that women and children of 3 Americans at
                    Fowyang, Anhwei, and 2 women in Chengchow area were evacuating and expressed
                    opinion that other missionaries who had elected to remain are prepared to flee
                    at a moment’s notice. Drumright has informally notified Shensi provincial
                    authorities of possible influx of American refugees and has requested that
                    facilities be accorded them.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
